SET FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS = 0; -- Disable safety checks...


-- +================================================================================+
-- | 1. DEPARTMENT                                                                  |
-- | Purpose: Defines the functional areas of the bank (eg. IT, Loans, Operations). |
-- | Relationships: Linked to the 'employee' table.                                 |
-- +================================================================================+


-- +=====================================================================================+
-- | 2. BRANCH                                                                           |
-- | Purpose: Physical locations of the bank. Stores address and city info.              |
-- | Relationships: Linked to 'employee' (where they work) and 'account' (where opened). |
-- +=====================================================================================+


-- +=========================================================================+
-- | 3. EMPLOYEE                                                             |
-- | Purpose: All staff members. Includes their title and hire date.         |
-- | Relationships: Uses 'superior_emp_id' to create a management hierarchy. |
-- +=========================================================================+


-- +===========================================================================+
-- | 4. PRODUCT_TYPE                                                           |
-- | Purpose: High-level categories for bank offerings (eg. Accounts v Loans). |
-- | Relationships: Parent table to 'product'.                                 |
-- +===========================================================================+


-- +====================================================================================+
-- | 5. PRODUCT                                                                         |
-- | Purpose: Specific financial products offered (eg. Savings Account, Auto Loan).     |
-- | Relationships: Linked to the 'account' table to define what kind of account it is. |
-- +====================================================================================+


-- +======================================================================================+
-- | 6. CUSTOMER                                                                          |
-- | Purpose: The base table for anyone doing business with the bank.                     |
-- | Note: Stores common data like Tax ID (fed_id) and address for both people and firms. |
-- +======================================================================================+


-- +=============================================================================+
-- | 7. INDIVIDUAL                                                               |
-- | Purpose: Details specific to human customers (First/Last name, Birth date). |
-- | Relationships: Shared Primary Key with 'customer' (1-to-1 relationship).    |
-- +=============================================================================+


-- +===============================================================================+
-- | 8. BUSINESS                                                                   |
-- | Purpose: Details specific to corporate customers (Company name, Incorp date). |
-- | Relationships: Shared Primary Key with 'customer' (1-to-1 relationship).      |
-- +===============================================================================+


-- +=============================================================================+
-- | 9. OFFICER                                                                  |
-- | Purpose: Identifies the authorized person representing a Business customer. |
-- | Relationships: Links a person (officer) to a specific business (cust_id).   |
-- +=============================================================================+


-- +===============================================================================+
-- | 10. ACCOUNT                                                                   |
-- | Purpose: The central table holding balances and status for customer products. |
-- | Relationships: Connects a Customer, a Product, a Branch, and an Employee.     |
-- +===============================================================================+


-- +============================================================================+
-- | 11. TRANSACTION                                                            |
-- | Purpose: History of all money movement (deposits/withdrawals) in accounts. |
-- | Relationships: Every transaction must point to exactly one 'account_id'.   |
-- +============================================================================+


SET FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS = 1; -- Re-enable safety checks...